ns2:PrimaryTypeDefinition.ns1:desc: This MO represents a Cell and contains parameters needed by the cell. It also contains parameters for the mandatory common channels.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The value component of the RDN.

The channel number for the central downlink frequency. The mapping from channel number to physical frequency for specified E-UTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. The values that can be used depend on national, operator-specific frequency allocation as well as on the supported frequency band(s) in the RBS.
Note: Use the MO-action changeFrequency if the DL frequency shall be changed after the cell is initally setup. This attribute is dependent on and set together with earfcnul, the values are dependent and relate accoring to the form earfcnul=earfcndl+18000.
Resolution: 1 Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object disabled/enabled.

The channel number for the central uplink frequency. The mapping from channel number to physical frequency for specified E-UTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. The values that can be used depend on national, operator specific frequency allocation as well as on the supported frequency band(s) of the RBS.
Note: This attribute is dependent on and set together with earfcndl, the values are dependent and relate accoring to the form earfcnul=earfcndl+18000.
Resolution: 1 Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object disabled/enabled

The frame start offset of the cell.
Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object disabled/enabled.

The number of Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) resources available on the PUCCH channel. For 1.4 MHz system bandwidth the recommended value is 50.
Unit: - Resolution: 1 Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object unlocked. Note: The parameter will take effect when System Information is updated.

The number of Scheduling Request (SR) resources available on the PUCCH channel. For 1.4 MHz system bandwidth the recommended value is 50.
Unit: - Resolution: 1 Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object unlocked. Note: The parameter will take effect when System Information is updated.

The downlink channel bandwidth in the cell.
Valid values: 1400, 3000, 5000, 10000, 15000, 20000
Unit: 1 kHz Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object disabled/enabled.

The uplink channel bandwidth in the cell.
Valid values: 1400, 3000, 5000, 10000, 15000, 20000
Unit: 1 kHz Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object disabled/enabled.

Defines the maximum distance from the base station where a connection to a UE can be setup and/or maintained.
Unit: km Resolution: 1 Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object unlocked

The total number of PRBs generated by Air Interface Load Generator in the DL direction for load of higher priority than the real UEs load
Unit: - Condition: Continuous measurement on TTI granularity on cell level Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: - Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of PRBs generated by Air Interface Load Generator in DL for artificial load, both for high and low priority load.
Unit: - Condition: Continuous measurement on TTI granularity on cell level Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: - Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of PRBs generated by Air Interface Load Generator in UL for artificial load, both for high and low priority load
Unit: - Condition: Continuous measurement on TTI granularity on cell level Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: - Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to WCDMA triggered by CS Fallback.
Unit: - Condition: A CS Fallback attempt is performed towards a WCDMA Frequency, defined as a RRC Connection Release with redirect information, due to a received CS Fallback Indicator set to CS Fallback Required in Initial Context Setup Request or UE Context Modification Request. Counter type: PEG Sampling rate: - Scanner: Primary Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to WCDMA triggered by CS Fallback Emergency.
Unit: - Condition: An Emergency CS Fallback attempt is performed towards a WCDMA Frequencies, defined as a RRC Connection Release with redirect information, due to a received CS Fallback Indicator set to CS Fallback High Priority in Initial Context Setup Request or UE Context Modification Request. Counter type: PEG Sampling rate: - Scanner: Primary Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to GSM triggered by CS Fallback Emergency.
Unit: - Condition: An Emergency CS Fallback attempt is performed towards a GSM Frequency Group, defined as a RRC Connection Release with redirect information, due to a received CS Fallback Indicator set to CS Fallback High Priority in Initial Context Setup Request or UE Context Modification Request. Counter type: PEG Sampling rate: - Scanner: Primary Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to GSM triggered by CS Fallback.
Unit: - Condition: A CS Fallback attempt is performed towards a GSM Frequency Group, defined as a RRC Connection Release with redirect information, due to a received CS Fallback Indicator set to CS Fallback Required in Initial Context Setup Request or UE Context Modification Request. Counter type: PEG Sampling rate: - Scanner: Primary Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Refers to an instance of AirIfLoadProfile. Assigns a AirIfLoadProfile to a cell.
Takes effect: Immediately
The state of the feature Air Interface Load Generator. Indicates if it is running or stopped.

The total number of failed E-RAB setup attempts due to downlink GBR overload for resources common to the eNodeB.
Unit: - Condition: Shall be stepped for each failed E-RAB Establishment attempt due to downlink GBR overload for resources common to the eNodeB. Counter type: PEG Sampling rate: - Scanner: Primary Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of failed E-RAB setup attempts due to uplink GBR overload for resources common to the eNodeB.
Unit: - Condition: Shall be stepped for each failed E-RAB Establishment attempt due to uplink GBR overload for resources common to the eNodeB. Counter type: PEG Sampling rate: - Scanner: Primary Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Distribution of the measured Timing Advance value at random access.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..9]%, [1]: [10..19]%, [2]: [20..29]%, [3]: [30..39]%, [4]: [40..49]%, [5]: [50..59]%, [6]: [60..69]%, [7]: [70..79]%, [8]: [80..89]%, [9]: [90..99]%, [10]: [100..109]%, [11]: [110..200]%
Unit: - Condition: When a successful random is done (RA Msg3 received) the counter covering the measured TA shall be incremented. Example: When a sample is measured at 50% it means that a successfull random acces has been done at 50% of the configured cell range. In this case bin 6 for the range 50..59% shall be increased. Counter type: PDF Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Distribution of the measured Timing Advance value for UL synchronized UEs
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..9]%, [1]: [10..19]%, [2]: [20..29]%, [3]: [30..39]%, [4]: [40..49]%, [5]: [50..59]%, [6]: [60..69]%, [7]: [70..79]%, [8]: [80..89]%, [9]: [90..99]%, [10]: [100..109]%, [11]: [110..200]%
Unit: - Condition: Periodically the actual TA of the UEs that are UL synchronized is monitored, one scan performed every 5 seconds. Example: When a sample is measured at 50% it means that an UL synchronized UE has a TA value at 50% of the configured cell range. In this case bin 6 for 50%..59% is increased. Counter type: PDF Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

For each System Information Block (SIB), indicates when the SIB content is changed, if system information change notification is broadcast prior to broadcast of updated system information.
Takes effect: Immediately

The System Information (SI) message to which each System Information Block (SIB) is mapped.
Note: SIB2 is always mapped to the SI message 1 according to 3GPP TS 36.331.
Takes effect: When EUtranCellFDD/TDD object is unlocked

The modification period, expressed in number of radio frames = modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle. See MO Paging for information about defaultPagingCycle.
Dependencies: modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle must be equal or less than 1024 radio frames. See MO Paging for information about defaultPagingCycle. Takes effect: When EUtranCellFDD/TDD object is unlocked

The periodicity of System Information (SI) messages. If a System Information Block (SIB) is not mapped to a SI message, the SI message is not transmitted.
Takes effect: When EUtranCellFDD/TDD object is unlocked.

Length of the System Information (SI) window within which each SI message is transmitted. Applies to all SI messages.
Note: An SI window of 1 ms may be configured only when a maximum of 5 SI messages is configured for broadcast by attribute mappingInfo, to avoid collision with SIB1 transmission in subframe #5.
Unit: ms Dependencies: siWindowLength * ‘transmitted number of SI-messages’ <= MIN(siPeriodicitySIx), i.e it must be possible schedule all SI messages within the shortest siPeriodicity time used. Takes effect: When EUtranCellFDD/TDD object is unlocked

The required minimum received Reference Symbol Received Power (RSRP) level in the E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1.
Unit: dBm Resolution: 2 Takes effect: Immediately

Contains the DRX sleep time in number of subframes for all UEs in the cell.
Unit: - Condition: Counter should be incremented every subframe for every UE in the cell for which DRX functionality in RRC_CONNECTED state is configured and the UE is in DRX sleep time. Time during ANR operation for a specific UE is excluded. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Contains the DRX total time in number of subframes for all UEs in the cell.
Unit: - Condition: Counter should be incremented every subframe for every UE in the cell for which DRX functionality in RRC_CONNECTED state is configured. Time during ANR operation for a specific UE is excluded. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Deprecated: Since L10B. Has no functional behaviour. Aggregated time for the downlink delay measure. One sample per successful transmission of a packet (PDCP SDU). The time for each sample is between reception of a packet (PDCP SDU) until the successful transmission of the corresponding MAC SDU.
Unit: ms Condition: Continuous measurement for UEs aggregated to cell level. Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: - Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Number of DRB packets for downlink Latency measurements when DRX is active and the UE has UL synchronization status "NOT synchronized".
Unit: - Condition: Measurement for UEs aggregated to cell level. Only PDCP SDUs that enters an empty buffer are measured. Samples during handover are excluded since they can distort the interpretation of the result (due to packet forwarding, the target cell might have to buffer data before it is possible to schedule the UE in the target cell, hence it would be an increased Latency measurement if it would be included. It would however not lead to a degraded performance for the end-user, due to packet forwarding). The samples are included Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

It would however not lead to a degraded performance for the end-user, due to packet forwarding). The samples are included Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Unit: - Condition: The effective DL Latency time comprises the time from PDCP DRB SDU entering the buffer until the first data has been transmitted to the UE. Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: - Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of RRC Connection Request attempts with establishment cause emergency.
Unit: - Condition: Stepped at reception of RRC message RRC Connection Request with establishment cause emergency. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of RRC Connection Request attempts with establishment cause highPriorityAccess
Unit: - Condition: Stepped at reception of RRC message RRC Connection Request with establishment cause highPriorityAccess Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Unit: - Condition: Stepped at reception of RRC message RRC Connection Request with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Data. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of RRC Connection Request attempts with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Signaling.
Unit: - Condition: Stepped at reception of RRC message RRC Connection Request with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Signaling. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of RRC Connection Request attempts with Establishment cause Mobile Terminating Access.
Unit: - Condition: Stepped at reception of RRC message RRC Connection Request with Establishment cause Mobile Terminating Access. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

This counters shows the accumulated active session time for all DRBs in a cell.
Unit: seconds Condition: Number of session seconds aggregated for DRBs in a cell. A DRB is said to be Â´in sessionÂ´ if data on a DRB (UL or DL) has been transferred during the last 100 ms. Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: - Scanner: Primary Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The sum of the contributions from each UE in the cell of the number of active DRBs in the downlink direction.
Unit: - Condition: Each TTI, the counter shall be increased wih the number of DRBs that are considered active (i.e. that have data in the downlink buffer). Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: - Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The sum of the contributions from each UE in the cell of the number of active DRBs in the uplink direction.
Unit: - Condition: Each TTI, the counter shall be increased wih the number of DRBs that are considered active (i.e. that are considered to have data in the uplink buffer). Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: - Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of Initial Context Setup Establishment attempts.
Unit: - Condition: Stepped for each S1 message Initial Context Setup Request. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of Initial Context Setup Establishment successes
Unit: - Condition: Stepped for each Initial Context that is successfully established. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to CDMA2000.
Unit: - Condition: A RRC Connection Release with redirect information to CDMA2000. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to GERAN.
Unit: - Condition: A RRC Connection Release with redirect information to GERAN. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to UTRA FDD.
Unit: - Condition: A RRC Connection Release with redirect information to UTRA FDD. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Number of attempts for handover to a cell better than the serving cell, before handover is attempted to the next best cell. If there is no next best cell in the UE report, handover to the best cell is attempted repeatedly.
Takes effect: Immediately.

Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards UTRAN.
Takes effect: Object lock/unlock

Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards GERAN.
Takes effect: Object lock/unlock

Contains cell re-selection information common for cell re-selection towards CDMA2000. This is controlled by the licensing MO Cdma2000SessionContinuity. The SIB8 distribution and information is also controlled by other licenses.
Takes effect: Object lock/unlock

Contains a list of EUtranCellRelation managed object instances that reserves this managed object instance.
Dependencies: The managed object cannot be deleted if it is reserved.

Contains cell re-selection information common for intra-frequency, inter-frequency and/ or inter-RAT cell re-selection.
Takes effect: Object lock/unlock

Specifies if uplink interference management is enabled or disabled.
Takes effect: Object unlocked

Contains all access barring information.
Takes effect: Immediately

Indicates if the cell is barred and should not be accessible to random UEs.
Takes effect: Immediately

Deprecated: Since L11A. Replaced by: primaryPlmnReserved and additionalPlmnReservedList Indicates if the cell is reserved for operator use.
The first index is for the primary Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) of the cell.
Takes effect: Immediately

Deprecated: Replaced by dlConfigurableFrequencyStart. Since L11B. The start frequency offset for allocating resources when the downlink interference management is disabled. Expressed as a percentage of the available bandwidth.
Unit: Percentage Resolution: 1 Dependencies: SchDevice:dlInterferenceManagementActive shall be disabled before this parameter takes effect. Takes effect: Immediately.

Specifies if the downlink interference management is enabled or disabled.
Takes effect: Object unlocked

Deprecated: Since L12A. Planned to be removed. The number of Orthogonal Frequency-Division Multiplexing (OFDM) symbols used for the Physical Downlink Control Channel (PDCCH).
Unit: OFDM Symbols Resolution: 1 Takes effect: Immediately.

Limits UE uplink transmission power in the serving cell and calculates the parameter Pcompensation (defined in 3GPP TS 36.304) for cell selection. The attribute is broadcast in SIB1.
Value 1000 means the parameter is not included in system information.
Takes effect: Immediately

The nominal component of the UE transmit power for Physical Uplink Control Channel (PUCCH).
Unit: dBm Resolution: 1 Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Immediately.

The nominal component of the UE transmit power for Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).
Unit: dBm Resolution: 1 Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Immediately.

Refers to an instance of QciTable and assigns a QciTable to a cell. The QciTable defines Quality of Service Class Indicator (QCI) to use in the cell.
Refers to the QciTable instance corresponding to Local Distinguished Name (LDN) = ManagementElement=1, ENodeBFunction=1, QciTable=default
Dependencies: It is assumed that the QciTable MO has been created. Takes effect: New connection.

The first root sequence number for Random Access Channel (RACH) preamble generation. RACH root sequence is broadcast as a part of system information distribution and used for preamble detection. See definition for logical root sequence number in 3GPP TS 36.211.
Resolution: 1 Disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. Takes effect: Object unlocked.

Unit: ms Condition: Each TTI, the counter shall be incremented when there was a need to schedule DRB data in the downlink. Counter type: PEG Sampling rate: Per ms Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Unit: ms Condition: The counter shall be increased with 1 for each UE that was scheduled with SRB/DRB data in the downlink. Counter type: ACC Sampling rate: Per TTI Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

Unit: - Condition: Stepped at reception of S1 message UE Context Release Command with internal cause codes considered abnormal (Radio Connection with UE is lost; Handover failure for the UE; UE pre-emption) when the RBS initiated the release. It can also be stepped at transmission of Reset message by the RBS, or when a cell owned by that RBS is disabled (and that leads to internal RBS UE Context Release). Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of abnormal UE Contexts Releases initiated by the RBS and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
Unit: - Condition: If there was data in the buffer at the time of release, then at reception of S1 message UE Context Release Command with internal cause codes considered abnormal (Radio Connection with UE is lost; Handover failure for the UE; UE pre-emption) when the RBS initiated the release. It can also be stepped at transmission of Reset message by the RBS, or when a cell owned by that RBS is disabled (and that leads to internal RBS UE Context Release). Counter type: PEG Scanner: Primary Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of abnormal UE context releases by the eNB due cell down time (manual intervention) and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
Unit: - Condition: Stepped for each UE that is lost due to cell down time (manual intervention). Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of abnormal UE Context Releases initiated by the eNB due to handover execution failure and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
Unit: - Condition: If there was data in the buffer at the time of release, and the release is due to that executed handover fails and the UE is considered dropped. Counter type: PEG Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner Counter is reset after measurement period: Yes

The total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNB due to S1 interface down and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
